<sect1 version="5.0" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
		>
	<title id="create-project">Creating a project</title>

	<para>
		Each Forge user can create a project. Simply open the link
		<emphasis role="bold">My space</emphasis>
		in the navigation menu and choose
		<emphasis role="bold">Create project.</emphasis>
	</para>

	<figure>
		<title>Create project menu</title>

		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata align="center" fileref="04-00-CreateProjectMenu.png"
					width="250px" />
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	</figure>

	<para>After starting the project creation application, proceed as
		follows:</para>

	<itemizedlist>
		<listitem>
			<para>Enter the project name.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Enter the project identifier.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Add the project to an existing organization or to a new
				organization to be created by the user (editable drop-down list in
				order to add new organizations).</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Enter a project description.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Choose a project license.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Enter a project description.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Choose whether the project is public or private.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>You can choose an image to represent the project icon. If no
				image is provided, a Novaforge image will be used by default.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>Choose a project template.</para>
		</listitem>

		<listitem>
			<para>click on "Add" button then validate your choice.</para>
		</listitem>
	</itemizedlist>

	<para>The following figure shows the project creation screen:</para>

	<figure>
		<title>Create project</title>

		<mediaobject>
			<imageobject>
				<imagedata align="center" fileref="04-01-CreateProject.png"
					width="350px" />
			</imageobject>
		</mediaobject>
	</figure>
</sect1>